            h4 Special Signal: Checking if a Process Exists
            
            p You can use a <i>‚Äúzero signal‚Äù</i> to check if a process is running ‚Äî without killing it.
            pre(class="bg-light")
                code.
                    > kill -0 PID

            p <strong>Return values:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><b>0</b> ‚Äî the process exists and is accessible.</li>
                <li><b>1</b> ‚Äî the process does not exist or you lack permission.</li>
            </ul>

            p üí° <b>Pro tip</b>: <code>kill -0</code> does not send any signal ‚Äî it only checks process existence and permissions!

            p Since the command itself doesn't print any output, you can check its result using the <code>echo $?</code> command, which displays the <i>exit status</i> of the <i>last executed command</i>, or use it <i>directly in a shell script</i> with conditional statements (<code>if/else</code>):
            pre(class="bg-light")
                code.
                    if kill -0 1234 2&gt;/dev/null; then
                        echo "Process 1234 is running"
                    else
                        echo "Process 1234 not found"
                    fi

